id: AIC-SYNC-001
type: module
owner: business
extends: project.intent

module: aic sync
command: aic sync <ComponentName> --language <language>
description: >
  Syncs code changes back to component.intent.
  Code is the source of truth after a manual fix.
  AI compares current code against current intent,
  identifies gaps, and suggests intent updates.
  Developer approves before any changes are written.

behaviors:
  - id: AIC-SYNC-001-B1
    intent: |
      Validate AIC is initialised and git is present.
      Validate component exists in specified language folder.
      Validate a lockfile exists — if not suggest aic compile first.

  - id: AIC-SYNC-001-B2
    intent: |
      Read current component.intent and current generated code file.
      Send both to configured AI provider with this instruction:
        "Compare this code against this intent file.
         Identify anything in the code that is not captured in the intent.
         Suggest updated or new intent sections only for what changed.
         Return only the YAML sections that need updating."
      This is the only LLM call in the entire command.

  - id: AIC-SYNC-001-B3
    intent: |
      Print the AI suggested intent changes clearly to terminal.
      Show side by side where possible:
        OLD intent section
        SUGGESTED intent section
      Do not write anything to component.intent yet.
      Ask developer to approve or reject.

  - id: AIC-SYNC-001-B4
    intent: |
      If --approve flag present apply suggested changes to component.intent.
      Merge suggested YAML sections into existing component.intent.
      Do not overwrite the entire file — only update changed sections.
      Update lockfile after successful write.
      Print success message confirming what was updated.

  - id: AIC-SYNC-001-B5
    intent: |
      If --reject flag present discard suggestions.
      component.intent unchanged.
      Inform developer no changes were made.

  - id: AIC-SYNC-001-B6
    intent: |
      Without --approve or --reject flag:
      Generate and show suggestions only.
      Print approval and rejection commands below suggestions.
      Do not prompt interactively — just show the commands.

  - id: AIC-SYNC-001-B7
    intent: |
      After successful --approve update lockfile:
        New intent hash from updated component.intent
        New code hash from current code file
        Sync timestamp
      This clears DRIFT state in aic status.

journeys:
  - actor: Developer
    trigger: Made hotfix in code, runs aic sync
    outcome: |
      AI compares code vs intent.
      Suggested intent updates shown.
      Developer runs with --approve.
      component.intent updated with only the changed sections.
      aic status shows IN SYNC.

  - actor: Developer
    trigger: Runs aic sync --approve without running sync first
    outcome: |
      No suggestions exist yet.
      Clear message — run sync first without --approve to generate suggestions.

  - actor: Developer
    trigger: Code perfectly matches intent
    outcome: |
      AI reports no gaps found.
      No suggestions generated.
      component.intent untouched.
      Clean message printed.

failure-modes:
  - scenario: No lockfile
    response: Exit code 1 — suggest aic compile first

  - scenario: AI provider not configured
    response: Exit code 1 — suggest filling aic.config.json

  - scenario: AI provider call fails
    response: Exit code 2 — no changes made

  - scenario: component.intent write fails
    response: Exit code 2 — suggestions preserved, show path error

  - scenario: No suggestions file when --approve run
    response: Exit code 1 — run sync first to generate suggestions